cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with resource allocation in 5G cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a combinatorial auction mechanism, which is a topic related to game theory and optimization. Hence, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the issue of inter-slice isolation, which is related to system control and automation, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of virtualization for 5G networks, which is a topic related to multimedia and human-computer interaction, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible category.
